hed look. Wisps of smoke drift past the windows and around the cab. The yellow cab’s occupants are then shown once more from the front, sitting behind the split windshield. The driver faces the road, and the passenger smiles beside him, both appearing comfortable and untroubled.\n\nA wider view shows the contrast between the two taxis. The yellow taxi speeds away across the open roadway in the foreground, while the green taxi remains behind on the shoulder, partly hidden by a large cloud of smoke. The yellow cab exits the scene, leaving the disabled green cab alone by the curb beneath the clear blue sky and distant high-rises.\n\nA tight front view of the smoky green taxi shows the “TAXI” roof sign above the windshield. The driver’s face fills the center, frowning with the cigarette at his mouth. Behind him, a small pair of red fuzzy dice hangs from the rearview area. Smoke curls around the cab and drifts across the glass, reinforcing that the vehicle has broken down.\n\nThe final roadway is an airport approach. The yellow taxi drives away from the viewer down the center of a broad road between low airport buildings. An overhead green sign reads “Departing Flights” with downward arrows. A small airplane is visible in the sky to the left. As the taxi continues forward, it visually gives way to a large floating Duracell battery on the road. The black cylindrical battery body appears with the white word “DURACELL” across its side. A copper-colored top section slides in and attaches to the black body, forming the familiar Duracell copper-top battery shape. Across the bottom of the screen, white text appears: “You Can’t Top The Copper Top.”",
